In this proclamation issued by President Donald J. Trump on April 30, 2020, he emphasizes the strength and loyalty of the United States as a nation. He highlights the ideals and values that Americans hold dear, such as freedom, independence, self-government, and a commitment to their shared destiny. The proclamation also acknowledges the sacrifices and dedication of healthcare workers, first responders, and other essential workers during the global pandemic. President Trump declares May 1st as Loyalty Day, a day to honor the United States and its values, and encourages Americans to learn more about the nation's history. He also urges government officials to display the flag of the United States on all government buildings and grounds on that day.